properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 17 at 2:55PM CST until January 19 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTER STORM TO BRING SNOW AND WIND TO NORTHEAST WISCONSIN...

.A strengthening area of low pressure is forecast to move from
the central Plains into the Great Lakes tonight into Saturday.
Snow is expected to reach central Wisconsin late this afternoon,
become locally heavy at times tonight and gradually diminish
Saturday afternoon. A little freezing rain or sleet may also mix
in at times tonight over central and east-central Wisconsin.
Total snow amounts of 5 to 8 inches are expected. Increasing west
to northwest winds on Saturday afternoon could also produce
blowing and drifting of the snow.

* WHAT...Snow is expected. Total snow accumulations of 5 to 8
inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph creating areas of
blowing and drifting snow.

* WHERE...Portions of central, east central, north central and
northeast Wisconsin.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Patchy blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility on Saturday afternoon.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A band of moderate to heavy snow is
expected to move across the region this evening. Visibilities in
the band of heavy snow may drop as low as a quarter to half
mile, along with snowfall rates of 1 to 2 inches per hour.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST SUNDAY
